'''Jelšovec''' ({{lang-hu|Jelsöc}}) is a village and municipality in the [[Lučenec District]] in the [[Banská Bystrica Region]] of [[Slovakia]].

==History==
In [[history|historical records]], the [[village]] was first mentioned in 1573 (''Jelsewcz'', ''Jelsoch''). It belonged to Somoskō castle an in the 17th century to [[Halič]]. From 1938 to 1945, it belonged to [[Hungary]].

